President Obama has announced the formation of a Presidential Delegation to attend the Special Olympics World Games in Los Angeles. The delegation will be led by First Lady Michelle Obama, who will give remarks at the opening ceremony. The games will feature 7,000 athletes and 3,000 coaches from 170 countries. The delegation will also include members of the United States House of Representatives Maxine Waters, Adam Schiff, Janice Hahn, and Alan Lowenthal.